The evidence with the title 'Does down syndrome justify abortion? - The New York Times ' says Sep 4, 2015  ... After the doctors gave us the news , they casually told us how an in utero diagnosis of Down syndrome meant perhaps a 50-50 chance of miscarriage or  ... Though precise numbers are unavailable , at least two-thirds and as many as 90 percent of fetuses found to have Down syndrome in utero are aborted. 
